verbose_text: XREF_BIBR cAMP synthesis, and thus indirectly its signaling, is promoted by stimulation of the G-protein-coupled dopamine receptor D1 and adenosine receptor A2, whereas synthesis is inhibited by dopamine stimulation of dopamine receptor D2.
